      <bioghist id="aspace_2971c2ca2c323a30f8ab2ec69c357356">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Dyer White (1762-1841) was a lawyer, judge, and revenue collector in New Haven, Connecticut. He founded his law firm in 1785.</p>
         <p>White married Susannah Whittesley White (1766-1796) in 1791, Hannah Wetmore White (1773-1830) in 1801, and Eunice Pomeroy White (1777-1869) in 1832. With Hannah White, he had one son, Henry White (1803-1880).</p>
      </bioghist>
      <prefercite id="aspace_a6f61b40f51d036766eb42ef872d1ec1">
